BadWhateverException - Exception in <Unnamed>
BadWhateverException is thrown every time you try to create a Whatever with a negative parameter.

Every exception has a default constructor which simply calls the default constructor of the parent.
BadWhateverException(String) - Constructor for exception BadWhateverException
Every exception also has a constructor with a string parameter that allows you to make your program print out that message when this exception occurs.
